physical_appearance: This is a pictorial of a child leaning on a ledge looking afar with his/her left hand on her head. Above him/her is a traditional wooden bird cage. Discolouration of the print has occurred, and the backing on which the print is mounted on has brown spotting as well.
sgcool_label_text: Ho Koon Sang was a member of the Photographic Society of Singapore and an Associate of the Royal Photographic Society in London. This photograph was part of a set of 12 prints sent to the Royal Photographic Society in 1956.
